Intrinsic apoptosis signaling (primitive) is a subtype of signaling [biological]: A processin which an intracellular signal is conveyed to trigger the apoptotic death of a cell. The process starts with reception of an intracellular signal (e.g. DNA damage, endoplasmic reticulum stress, oxidative stress etc.).
This process is crucially regulated by permeabilization of the mitochondrial outer membrane (MOMP).
